UNITED STATES NAVAL SUPPORT ACTIVITY, TAIPEI REPUBLIC OF CHINA BOX 25 APO 63 SAN FRANCISCO, CALIFORNIA
USNSAT-35/RCW:aw 4570 Ser: 3373
12 June 1962
From:
Commanding Officer, U.S. Naval Support Activity, Taipei,
Republic of China
To: Distribution List
Subj: Local Area Screening List No. N122-62-63044
Ref: (a) BUSANDA Manual, para 28116
Encl: (1) List of available excess personal property
1. The excess personal property listed on enclosure (1) is available for transfer within the Federal Government and for donation to authorized donees in accordance with the following provisions.
a. Screening Period. The utilization screening period is twenty
(20) days. Transfer requests must be received prior to the expiration
date. Donation screening will be accomplished during a 20 day period
following utilization screening
140:112.213.82
b. Inspection. The property will be available for inspection from
1300 to 1500 Monday thru Friday. Whenever possible, the custodian
should be contacted in advance to arrange for inspection.
(Phone 43261 ASHLEY, SK])
c. Condition Code. The condition code shown conforms to that specified by regulations of the General Services Administration and by reference (a).
1
d. Submission of requests. Requests for material will be submitted directly to the address indicated on enclosure (1) and will include the list number, the item number, the FSN and noun nomenclature, the quantity and the destination. Appropriations chargable for fair value handling costs, and transportation will be included, if appropriate.
51.6. 20 12214
e. Priority of Issue. Requests for property will be given priority follows:
